Key Match Events: Maxime Crépeau made four excellent saves to keep a clean sheet against France.
Liam Millar's shot hit the crossbar early in the second half.
Kingsley Coman missed an open header in front of goal.
Moïse Bombito effectively marked Kylian Mbappé when he came on as a substitute.
Pre-Game Insights: Didier Deschamps made three changes to the French lineup, including starting Olivier Giroud in his last international match in France.
Jesse Marsch opted to start Maxime Crépeau in goal over Dayne St. Clair.
Post-Match Reflections: Jesse Marsch praised his team's performance and noted the improvement from their previous match against the Netherlands.
Marsch highlighted the development of the partnership between Moïse Bombito and Derek Cornelius in defense.
Stephen Eustáquio and Ismaël Koné were praised for their midfield performances.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was held in Bordeaux.
Canada had 55% possession in the first half and a 92% passing accuracy.
This was Jesse Marsch's second game as Canada's head coach.
